r any call to `import_module_from_file` completes, `sys.path` contains more entries than it did before the call. The fix must ensure `sys.path` is the same length before and after every call to `import_module_from_file`, even when the import raises an exception.\n\n**Bug 2** \u2014 Importing a provider file whose name matches a stdlib module (e.g. a file named `json.py`) causes subsequent `import json` calls elsewhere in the process to return the provider file instead of the real stdlib module. After the fix, importing any provider file via `import_module_from_file` must not replace an already-registered module in `sys.modules`.\n\n**Bug 3** \u2014 `_find_package_root` has no upper bound on how far up the directory tree it walks. After the fix, `_find_package_root` must accept a boundary argument and must not walk above it. The `import_module_from_file` function must accept a `provider_root` parameter and pass it as the boundary. The `discover_and_import` function must pass its `root` as the `provider_root` when calling `import_module_from_file`.\n\n**Bug 4** \u2014 With `reload=True`, concurrent calls to reader methods such as `_list_tools()` occasionally return empty results even though the provider has tools registered. After the fix, no concurrent caller must ever observe an empty or partially-rebuilt components dict during a reload.\n\n**Bug 5** \u2014 With `reload=True`, N concurrent requests each trigger a full `_load_components` call, even when another concurrent caller just completed a reload. After the fix, concurrent reload requests must be deduplicated: a caller that waited for the lock must skip `_load_components` if the lock holder already completed a reload.\n\n**Bug 6** \u2014 When `FileSystemProvider._load_components` runs with a root path that does not exist, it silently produces zero components with no warning. After the fix, `_load_components` must log a warning when `self._root` does not exist, so that typos in the root path are visible.\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Do not modify any files under `tests/`.\n- Existing tests must continue to pass.\n- The `reload=False` (default) mode must remain unaffected by the concurrency fixes.\n\n## Verification\n\n    python3 /tests/verify.py\n\nThe repository is at `/testbed`.\n\n\n## Gold Decomposition Guide\nsub_tasks:\n  - id: investigate-and-fix-import-machinery\n    description: >\n      Investigate the file-discovery module that handles importing Python\n      files as provider modules. Read the relevant source file under\n      src/fastmcp/server/providers/ and identify the three import-related\n      bugs described in the instruction (sys.path pollution, stdlib module\n      shadowing, and unbounded directory-tree walking). Implement fixes\n      for all three so that: the module path list is unchanged after every\n      import call, provider files never replace already-registered modules,\n      and the package-root search respects a caller-supplied boundary.\n      Update all call sites to pass the boundary through.\n    depends_on: []\n    parallel_group: fan-out\n\n  - id: investigate-and-fix-reload-logic\n    description: >\n      Investigate the provider class that manages reload-on-request\n      behaviour. Read the relevant source file under\n      src/fastmcp/server/providers/ and identify the three reload-related\n      bugs described in the instruction (race condition returning empty\n      results, redundant reloads under concurrency, and silent failure\n      when the root path does not exist). Implement fixes for all three\n      so that: concurrent readers never observe an empty component set,\n      only one actual reload runs per wave of concurrent requests, and a\n      warning is logged when the configured root directory is missing.\n    depends_on: []\n    parallel_group: fan-out\n\n  - id: verify-all-fixes\n    description: >\n      After both sets of fixes are applied, run the verification script\n      from the repository root to confirm all checks pass. If any check\n      fails, report which check failed and why.\n    depends_on: [investigate-and-fix-import-machinery, investigate-and-fix-reload-logic]\n    parallel_group: synthesize\n"}}'; sleep 86400) | kimi --config-file /tmp/kimi-config.json --wire --yolo 2>/dev/null | (while IFS= read -r line; do echo "$line" >> /logs/agent/kimi-cli.txt; case "$line" in *'"id":"1"'*) break ;; esac; done; kill 0 2>/dev/null)
